=head1 Gnome::Gtk4::R-ShortcutManager

![](images/shortcutmanager.png)

=head1 Description

The U<Gnome::Gtk4::R-ShortcutManager> interface is used to implement
shortcut scopes.

This is important for B<Gnome::Gtk4::R-Native> widgets that have their
own surface, since the event controllers that are used to implement
managed and global scopes are limited to the same native.

Examples for widgets implementing U<Gnome::Gtk4::R-ShortcutManager> are
B<Gnome::Gtk4::Window> and B<Gnome::Gtk4::Popover>.

Every widget that implements U<Gnome::Gtk4::R-ShortcutManager> will be used as a
C<GTK_SHORTCUT_SCOPE_MANAGED>.

